					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-686053#post-1837711</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-686053/scp-1363#post-1837711</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 22 Aug 2013 02:30:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Abettik</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1700758</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Really like this. +1</p> <p>Professionally written, weird, creepy, misdirection (thought this was a 'normal' virus thing at first), and a cool 'historical' backstory.</p> <p>Wouldn't change a thing. Except maybe that the lesions shouldn't 'change,' it should just make new ones. So after a while you start running out of skin to talk with until it heals. :-P</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-686053#post-1837625</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-686053/scp-1363#post-1837625</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 21 Aug 2013 23:20:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dr Cuddles</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1536640</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The technical aspect is well written, and an interesting idea, so +1. I was leaning toward a neutral-vote, because it only partially grabbed my interest. I think the demon core backstory is more than an easter egg. Because of the dates I figured it had to do with nuclear research, but it didn't really make much sense to me until I realized who the dead persons were.</p> <p>Some details:<br /> ''refrigerated'': I suggest ''frozen'' for long-term-storage.<br /> ''appear to be unaware of their nature'': this does not quite fit with the last sentence of interview.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
